Juventus beat Napoli 2-0 in a
matchup of unbeaten teams in Italian soccerâ€™s Serie A, while
 Bayern Munich  set a German record with its eighth straight win.  Jose Caceres and Paul Pogba scored in the final 10 minutes
as defending champion Juventus won for the seventh time in eight
games to move three points ahead of Napoli.  Thomas Mueller  scored twice as Bayern routed Hamburg 5-0 to
set the Bundesliga mark for wins to open a season. Second-place
Frankfurt beat Hannover 3-1, while Schalke moved into third
